Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring Diane Masariu
2 Carter.
3 Whereas, Diane Masariu Carter has been a presence at the
4 Indiana Statehouse as a staff member and advocate for fifty
5 years;
6 Whereas, Before joining Faegre Drinker Consulting, Diane
7 Masariu Carter worked at the Statehouse for thirty-one years,
8 including as Principal Clerk of the House of Representatives
9 during the 2003 and 2004 Legislative Sessions;
10 Whereas, Diane Masariu Carter also served as Policy
11 Director for the Indiana House Democratic Caucus and as
12 Administrative Assistant for two House Speakers and other
13 Democratic Leaders;
14 Whereas, Diane Masariu Carter steadfastly participates in
15 her community through civic activities such as being a member
16 of the St. Christopher Catholic Parish, a past member of the
17 Parks Board of the Town of Speedway, and has been the
18 recipient of numerous advocacy awards;
2026 DR 3850/DI aj

2
1 Whereas, In 2004, Diane Masariu Carter was awarded a
2 Sagamore of the Wabash by Governor Joe Kernan;
3 Whereas, In 2023, Diane Masariu Carter was awarded the
4 Allen C. Steere Award by the Governmental Affairs Society of
5 Indiana for her exceptional mentorship, being a role model,
6 and personifying the standards of conduct contained in the
7 Society's Statement of Ethical Principles;
8 Whereas, Diane Masariu Carter has mentored countless
9 Statehouse staff and contemporaries; and
10 Whereas, Diane Masariu Carter is one of the most
11 respected people at the Indiana Statehouse, having developed
12 strong relationships on both sides of the aisle along with a deep
13 understanding of the legislative process: Therefore,
14 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
15 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
16
17 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors Diane Masariu
18 Carter for her years of mentorship and advocacy.
19 SECTION 2. That the Secretary of the Senate is directed to
20 transmit copies of this Resolution to Diane Masariu Carter.
